# GMP Platform — Cursor Hard Rules
# Read this file FIRST in every session. Do not override. Do not add exceptions.
# If a rule blocks your implementation: STOP, state the conflict, ask for guidance.

# ── STACK ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- Backend: Python 3.12+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.x (async), Alembic, PostgreSQL
- Frontend: React 18+, TypeScript (strict mode), Vite
- Testing: pytest, pytest-asyncio, httpx AsyncClient
- Scheduler: APScheduler (AsyncIOScheduler) — 6-hour overdue check interval
- Auth: JWT (access + refresh tokens), bcrypt

# ── ARCHITECTURE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Pattern: Modular Monolith — one process, one database, strict module boundaries.

Modules: qms | mes | equipment | training | env_monitoring | lims
Foundation (core/): auth | audit | esig | workflow | documents | notify | integration

# ── MODULE BOUNDARY RULES — HARD STOPS ───────────────────────────────────────

## Rule 1: No cross-module Python imports
app.modules.X CANNOT import from app.modules.Y — ever.
Single carved-out exception (documented and intentional):
  - `app.modules.lims.services` may late-import `app.modules.qms.services`
    inside function scope for the OOS -> Deviation hook only.
  - No module-level import and no other cross-module imports are allowed.

  WRONG:  from app.modules.qms.models import CAPA   # inside app.modules.mes.*
  RIGHT:  store the reference as String(36) UUID and resolve at the API/service layer

Foundation imports from any module are ALLOWED:
  OK:  from app.core.auth.models import User
  OK:  from app.core.notify.services import NotificationService

## Rule 2: No cross-module ForeignKey constraints
ForeignKey() references may only point to:
  (a) tables owned by the SAME module
  (b) foundation layer tables (users, sites, workflow_instances, electronic_signatures, documents)

  WRONG:  deviation_id: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(ForeignKey("deviations.id"))   # MES → QMS
  RIGHT:  linked_deviation_id: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(String(36), nullable=True)

## Rule 3: Hook registry — core/tasks.py has zero module model imports
  WRONG:  from app.modules.qms.models import CAPA   # inside core/tasks.py
  RIGHT:  each module owns its tasks.py; main.py registers hooks at startup

# ── GMP / REGULATORY — NON-NEGOTIABLE ────────────────────────────────────────

## Rule 4: Server-set timestamps only
Audit trail fields are ALWAYS set server-side in UTC.
  WRONG:  accepting performed_at from the request body
  RIGHT:  performed_at = datetime.now(timezone.utc)  # set in the service layer

## Rule 5: Append-only audit trail
audit_events rows are NEVER updated or deleted.

## Rule 6: Append-only test results
Corrections require a NEW TestResult referencing the original (invalidated) result.

## Rule 7: Electronic signatures require re-authentication
  WRONG:  reusing the existing session token
  RIGHT:  re-enter username + password via ESignatureService.sign()

## Rule 8: Status flags must be maintained by the system that owns them
If a model column exists (e.g. CalibrationRecord.is_overdue, TrainingAssignment.status="overdue"),
the scheduler MUST write to it. Dead columns are a GMP data integrity finding.

## Rule 9: Overdue hooks MUST notify — counting without alerting is broken
After counting overdue records, call NotificationService.send_rule_based().
The notify infrastructure is already wired. Use it.

# ── SECURITY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Rule 10: No wildcard CORS in production
  WRONG:  allow_origins=["*"]
  RIGHT:  allow_origins=[settings.FRONTEND_URL]  when ENVIRONMENT != "development"

## Rule 11: create_all is dev/test only
  WRONG:  await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.create_all)  # unconditional
  RIGHT:  guard with  if settings.ENVIRONMENT != "production"

## Rule 12: No hardcoded secrets
All credentials via environment variables only.

# ── ALEMBIC MIGRATIONS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Rule 13: Every schema change needs a migration
create_all is dev-only. Production always uses alembic upgrade head.

## Rule 14: Silent exception swallowing in migrations is forbidden
  WRONG:  except Exception: pass
  RIGHT:  except Exception as exc: logger.warning("Could not drop %s: %s", constraint, exc)

## Rule 15: Every migration must have a valid downgrade()

# ── QUALITY GATES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

These must pass after every change. CI blocks on failure.

  pytest backend/tests/test_architecture_boundaries.py   # boundary enforcement
  python chaos.py                                         # reliability simulation

When adding a new module:
  1. Add it to MODULE_NAMES in test_architecture_boundaries.py
  2. Create modules/<name>/tasks.py with an overdue hook
  3. Import and register the hook in main.py lifespan
  4. Wire hook to NotificationService

# ── ECOSYSTEM SCOPE — WHAT WE BUILD vs. WHAT WE WIRE ────────────────────────

## Rule 16: Check before building — Replace vs. Integrate

Before implementing any new system or integration, determine which category it belongs to.

### ALWAYS REPLACE (build natively in the platform)
- QMS (TrackWise, Veeva QMS, MasterControl, ETQ, Qualio)
- MES / EBR (Syncade, Werum PAS-X, Rockwell PharmaSuite, Tulip)
- LIMS (LabVantage, STARLIMS, LabWare, SampleManager)
- Document Control (Veeva QDocs, Documentum, SharePoint GxP)
- Training / LMS (Veeva Training, ComplianceWire, MasterControl Training)
- Equipment / CMMS / Calibration (Blue Mountain RAM, SAP PM functionality)
- ELN (Benchling, IDBS, Signals Notebook)
- SPC / Analytics (JMP, Minitab, InfinityQS) — replace with built-in dashboards
- Serialization (TraceLink, SAP ATTP)
- Pharmacovigilance (Argus Safety, Veeva Safety)
- RIM (Veeva RIM)
- ERP quality modules (SAP QM, PP, PM) — replace functionality, keep data sync

### ALWAYS INTEGRATE (never build, only connect via IntegrationConnector)
- Process Control / DCS / SCADA (DeltaV, PCS7, ABB 800xA, Experion, PlantPAx)
- CDS / instrument firmware (Empower, Chromeleon, OpenLab, Unicorn)
- Environmental monitoring sensors (viewLinc, Vaisala, Dickson, Monnit, Kaye)
- ERP financial/HR layer (SAP Finance, HR, Payroll, Oracle ERP, Dynamics 365)
- Microbiology instruments (MYLA, BacT/Alert, VITEK 2)
- Cold chain hardware (Sensitech, Elpro, Mesa Labs, Controlant)
- Data historians (OSIsoft PI, Aspen IP21, GE Historian) — read-only data feed

### GOLDEN RULES
1. Hardware-bound systems = ALWAYS INTEGRATE, never replace
2. Financial/HR/Payroll layer = ALWAYS INTEGRATE, never replace
3. Software-only QMS/LIMS/LMS/DocControl = REPLACE outright
4. ERP quality modules = replace functionality, keep ERP data sync
5. Validate once = foundation validated once; modules validate functionally

## Rule 17: All external connections go through IntegrationConnector
Never hardcode third-party API calls in module code.
Use core/integration/models.py (IntegrationConnector, IntegrationDataFeed) for all
external system connections. This is the single point of integration governance.

# ── IF AMBIGUOUS — STOP AND ASK ──────────────────────────────────────────────

Do not guess. Do not pick the simpler path without flagging the trade-off.
State: (a) the ambiguity, (b) the two options, (c) the trade-off. Then wait.
